==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kneejoint
<hw>Knee"joint`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
joint of the knee.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A toggle joint; -- so called
because consisting of two pieces jointed to each other end to end,
making an angle like the knee when bent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kneejointed</ent>⟦br⟧
